{:component/id :orbiplex/artifact-delivery
 :component/title "Artifact Delivery"
 :component/type :node-attached-runtime
 :component/status :partial

 :summary
 "Host-owned artifact delivery and admission plane. Components submit one
 delivery envelope carrying artifact, delivery plan, and policy, plus
 explicit inbound/outbound artifact schema declarations; the host resolves
 recipients, executes fan-out and fallback plans, selects transports such as
 INAC or Agora, centralizes transport runtime, and dispatches inbound artifacts
 to exactly one authoritative acceptor."

 :must-implement
 [{:cap/id :artifact-delivery-runtime
   :title "Host-Owned Artifact Delivery Runtime"
   :kind :runtime
   :based-on ["doc/project/40-proposals/042-inter-node-artifact-channel.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/017-inter-node-artifact-channel/017-inter-node-artifact-channel.md"
              "doc/project/60-solutions/019-middleware/019-middleware.md"]
   :schemas ["artifact-delivery-envelope.v1"
             "artifact-delivery-result.v1"
             "artifact-delivery-status.v1"
             "artifact-delivery-recovery.v1"]
   :responsibilities
   ["Expose one component-facing artifact send surface"
    "Expose artifact.delivery.send as the component-facing host capability"
    "Keep transport connections centralized in the host"
    "Compile route tables from factory config, effective config, in-process manifests, and middleware module reports"
    "Return delivery ids for accepted asynchronous deliveries and expose delivery status lookup"
    "Keep core validation, normalization, recipient resolution, target deduplication, and outbound authorization synchronous and side-effect-free"
    "Persist accepted submissions and canonical expanded dispatch plans before transport execution"
    "Expose route table and conflict state to the operator"]
   :status :partial
   :notes
   ["Node now provides artifact-delivery-core, artifact-delivery, JSON schemas, schema-gate validators, daemon config, startup/effective-config validation, artifact.delivery.send, route/status APIs, deterministic ids, an in-memory test ledger, a SQLite runtime ledger at `<node-data-dir>/storage/artifact-delivery.sqlite` with explicit user_version migrations and PRAGMA setup, the Agora publish adapter, a local INAC direct short-circuit adapter, inbound acceptor registry conflict detection, pre-acceptor non-empty sha256 and inline byte-identity validation, a receiver-local inbound admission/refusal ledger, admission idempotency, admission status APIs/UI, Story-005 public Whisper candidate delivery through AD -> Agora, and regression coverage."
    "Deferred Artifact Delivery is a P055 consumer: `?mode=deferred` returns `deferred-operation.v1` with stable operation metadata, `audit/outcome-ref`, and a canonical operation-status URL; recovery preserves prior attempts in `retry/history` and returns schema-gated `artifact-delivery-recovery.v1`. The daemon also starts a background recovery worker by default, with interval, batch, and pass-deadline policy visible to operators."
    "Current production adapters are operationally inline-first. Referenced payload locations (`artifact/ref`, `artifact/href`) require an explicit resolver/fetch contract before a route can accept them."
    "Current runtime records and validates policy shape, but full generic enforcement of privacy, retry, timeout, retention, and operator-review semantics remains route/adapter/domain-specific until the later policy-enforcement layer lands."
    "Remote INAC peer transport, JSON-e Flow acceptor declaration, referenced payload resolver/fetch support, full generic delivery-policy enforcement, and private/direct Story-005 delivery are later layers."]}

  {:cap/id :artifact-delivery-outbound-authorization
